    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>
        It is not surprising that the human mind is capable of <i>reasoning</i> about complex properties like physics (e.g. "Will that stack of plates fall?") or navigation ability (e.g. "Can I get out of this maze?") &mdash; but perhaps such properties are also <b>spontaneously extracted</b> as a part of how we <b><i>see</i></b> the world in the first place?
    </p>
    <p>
